Pour the cold @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid.

Stir in the @Basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @Echalion shallot{1} into small pieces.

Trim the @green beans{80%g} and chop into thirds.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until browned all over, ~{6-8%minutes}. Turn occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Once the chicken has browned, add the shallot and fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @korma curry paste{50%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1} and @water{50%ml} for the curry.

Add the @creme fraiche{75%g} and green beans to the pan, stir together, then bring to the boil.

Simmer until the beans are tender and the chicken is cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== King Prawns Option ==

If you've chosen to add king prawns to your meal, simmer the curry for ~{2%minutes}, then stir in the @?king prawns{150%g} and cook for the remaining ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

== To Serve ==

When the curry is ready, taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between your #bowls{}. Top with the chicken korma style curry. Enjoy!